# 🐳 Docker Monitor CLI

Advanced Docker Resource Monitoring and Management CLI tool for DevOps engineers.

## ✨ Features

- 📊 **Real-time Resource Monitoring**: CPU, Memory, Network I/O, Block I/O
- 📋 **Container Management**: List, Start, Stop, Restart containers
- 🔍 **Detailed Inspection**: View container details and configuration
- 📜 **Log Viewing**: Fetch and follow container logs
- 📈 **Process Monitoring**: View running processes inside containers
- 🧹 **Pruning**: Clean up unused containers and resources
- 🎨 **Beautiful UI**: Rich terminal interface with colors and formatting
- 🚀 **Live Updates**: Watch mode for real-time statistics

## 📋 Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- Docker Engine 20.10+
- Docker SDK for Python
- Linux OS (Tested on Fedora)

## 🚀 Installation

### Method 1: Direct Installation (Recommended)

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/docker-monitor-cli.git
cd docker-monitor-cli

# Run installation script
chmod +x scripts/install.sh
./scripts/install.sh

# Or install manually
pip install -e .
